cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.IR. 

This paper is about developing a neural model for sentence simplification, which is a task related to natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses a neural programmer-interpreter approach, which involves training a neural network to perform specific operations, suggesting that it could also fit into the categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses benchmark corpora to evaluate the performance of the model, which could place it in the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper involves text simplification, which could also fit into the category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
